<br>
In the course of playing once a week with a group for the last 4 years, I have managed to get a troll warrior up to 44th level.  Recently, a friend of mine who had a warrior, but who doesn't play very much anymore, gave me a few new weapons.  To be honest, I play a SK as my main, so the duel weild thing hasn't been my primary concern.  I am MT for the group I play with, so I am not necessarily looking for damage as much as aggro.<br>
<br>
Here is the list...<br>
<br>
Wurmy 25/40 (Main Weapon up to now)<br>
Glimmering War Axe 10/25 (Main Offhand up to now)<br>
Seblite Croaking Dirk 10/18 (New)<br>
Mudman Enforcer 8/20 (New)<br>
Icepaw War Claw 9/24 Primary only (New)<br>
<br>
I can do math and figure out which ones have the best ratios, however, I have heard that speed is often more important than damage when it comes to keeping aggro off of those pansy clerics and enchanters.<br>
<br>
What do you suggest I use for maximum aggro.?  Thanks in advance.<br>
<br>
Thunkum Indagroan<br>
